This paper deals with the efficient processing of analytical queries on large amounts of data, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of cloud infrastructure for query processing, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of specialized techniques for tree execution plans suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper's focus on resource allocation and management for maximizing profit aligns with cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
